BAUCHI – As part of efforts to ensure a hitch-free Eid-el-Fitr celebration across the state, the police authorities in Bauchi State have ordered the deployment of officers, comprising conventional and other tactical teams of the Command. The Command also stated that it has put in place all the necessary logistics in all praying grounds as well as venues of events in the state. This was contained in a press statementby the Command PPRO, Ahmed Wakili and made available to newsmen in Bauchi. According to the PPRO,  visibility policing structures have been put in place in addition to patrols, particularly around residential areas, major highways, and government/private infrastructures. He stated that the Command is prepared to deal with hoodlums, political thugs and other disgruntled elements that may attempt to cause break down of law and order before during and after the festive period. “The Commissioner of Police extends his warm greetings to all Muslims and other citizens in the state as they celebrate EID-FITIR and enjoins them to co-operate with Police and other relevant security agencies in their efforts towards ensuring peaceful celebrations” ” They should report any suspicious person or object to the nearest Police Station or call the Command emergency phone numbers; 08151849417, 09053872273″ The statement read He said that the State Commissioner of police also assured the people of Bauchi State of the Command’s readiness to perform its statutory responsibility of protecting the lives and property of citizens in the state before, during and after the celebration. POLL “Umar Sanda promised that the Command will collaborate with other relevant Security Agencies and all critical stakeholders to ensure that, the celebration is peaceful and hitch-free” The statement added.